custom_view_definition:
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW identity.v_users AS
SELECT 
    -- 1. Base User Identity
    t.id,
    t.auth_id,
    t.name,
    t.email,
    t.mobile,
    t.details,
    t.created_at,
    t.updated_at,
    t.pref_organization_id,

    -- 2. Organization Context (from identity.organization_users)
    -- We join based on the user's PREFERRED organization
    ou.is_active,
    ou.status,
    ou.path AS org_path,
    ou.organization_id AS context_org_id,

    -- 3. Hydrated Foreign Keys (The "Custom" Logic)
    o.name AS organization_name,
    l.name AS location_name,
    m.name AS manager_name,

    -- 4. Computed/Frontend Helpers
    -- You can add extra logic here, e.g., combining names or formatting dates
    COALESCE(ou.is_active, false) AS "isActive"

FROM identity.users t

-- Join to Context: Get the org user record for the user's preferred org
LEFT JOIN identity.organization_users ou 
    ON t.id = ou.user_id 
    AND t.pref_organization_id = ou.organization_id

-- Hydrate Organization Name
LEFT JOIN identity.organizations o 
    ON ou.organization_id = o.id

-- Hydrate Location Name
LEFT JOIN identity.locations l 
    ON ou.location_id = l.id

-- Hydrate Manager Name (Self-Join to Users)
LEFT JOIN identity.users m 
    ON ou.manager_id = m.id;

custom_view_definition:
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW identity.v_teams AS
SELECT
    t.id,
    t.name,
    t.organization_id,
    o.name AS organization_name,
    
    t.location_id,
    l.name AS location_name,
    l.path AS location_path,
    
    t.details,
    t.created_at,
    t.updated_at,
    t.created_by,
    t.updated_by,

    -- List of users associated with this team
    (
        SELECT jsonb_agg(jsonb_build_object(
            'organization_user_id', ut.organization_user_id,
            'user_id', ou.user_id,
            'name', u.name,
            'email', u.email,
            'mobile', u.mobile,
            'last_assigned_at', ut.last_assigned_at
        ))
        FROM identity.user_teams ut
        JOIN identity.organization_users ou
            ON ou.id = ut.organization_user_id
        LEFT JOIN identity.users u
            ON u.id = ou.user_id
        WHERE ut.team_id = t.id
    ) AS team_users

FROM identity.teams t
JOIN identity.organizations o ON o.id = t.organization_id
LEFT JOIN identity.locations l ON l.id = t.location_id;

INTERVAL '90 days')", "description": "The number of new contacts in the last 90 days", "display_name": "New Contacts (Last 90 Days)"}, {"name": "new_contacts_last_365_days", "formula": "COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE DATE(created_at) >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '365 days')", "description": "The number of new contacts in the last 365 days", "display_name": "New Contacts (Last 365 Days)"}, {"name": "average_contact_age_days", "formula": "AVG(DATE_PART('day', AGE(CURRENT_DATE, DATE(created_at))))", "description": "The average age of contacts in days", "display_name": "Average Contact Age (Days)"}, {"name": "contacts_with_email", "formula": "COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE email IS NOT NULL AND email != '')", "description": "The number of contacts with an email address", "display_name": "Contacts with Email"}, {"name": "contacts_with_phone", "formula": "COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE phone IS NOT NULL AND phone != '' AND phone != '0')", "description": "The number of contacts with a phone number", "display_name": "Contacts with Phone"}, {"name": "contacts_with_both_email_phone", "formula": "COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE (email IS NOT NULL AND email != '') AND (phone IS NOT NULL AND phone != '' AND phone != '0'))", "description": "The number of contacts with both an email address and a phone number", "display_name": "Contacts with Email & Phone"}, {"name": "primary_contacts_count", "formula": "COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE is_primary = TRUE)", "description": "The number of primary contacts", "display_name": "Primary Contacts"}, {"name": "contacts_per_account_avg", "formula": "AVG(contacts_per_account)", "description": "The average number of contacts per account", "display_name": "Avg. Contacts per Account"}, {"name": "contacts_with_no_account", "formula": "COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE account_id IS NULL)", "description": "The number of contacts without an account", "display_name":
